1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,920
<i>Since when did we hire this baker?</i>

2
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,440
<i>Are you a "hit and run" guy?</i>

3
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:16,120
It was just
a "friends with benefits" thing.

4
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:18,000
-Are you hungry?
-Huh? Hungry for what?

5
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:19,720
Whoa, easy! You’ll get drunk.

6
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:21,320
I can handle this much.

7
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:26,720
and finally--

8
00:00:28,040 --> 00:00:28,920
200 drinks.

9
00:00:32,280 --> 00:00:34,000
I don’t sleep with just anyone.

10
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:35,920
<i>From now on, you have to call me…</i>

11
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:36,960
Pi Doc.

12
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:39,240
Nong Sailom.

13
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:40,920
Okay, Pi Doc.

14
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:50,040
Here’s a receipt.

15
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,120
The cakes are good,

16
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:54,160
but do you have less sweet ones?

17
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:57,160
Do you have keto or stevia cakes?

18
00:01:57,240 --> 00:02:00,800
I’m watching my weight but I can’t resist.

19
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:04,200
We don't have those yet,

20
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:06,480
but I'll let you know as soon as we do.

21
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,320
Thank you.

22
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,479
You’re welcome.

23
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:13,080
Auntie Phailin,

24
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:16,440
should I try making less sweet cakes?

25
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:19,360
Maybe we can use stevia instead of sugar

26
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:21,640
for health-conscious customers.

27
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,080
Of course.

28
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:26,600
I'll give you a free hand to try.

29
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,320
Thank you.

30
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:58,760
That’ll do.

31
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,120
What are you baking?

32
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:10,160
Banana cakes.

33
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:14,680
What?

34
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,800
Who kicked your ass this time?

35
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:17,880
Push off.

36
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,080
DinDin,

37
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:34,400
why the hell does this taste crappy?

38
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:38,200
Did you change my recipe?

39
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:41,800
No, no. It’s the same one.

40
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:44,040
I just cut down the sugar
and used stevia instead.

41
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,240
What for?

42
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:47,760
You’d be better spending
your time restocking the display!

43
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:50,400
Hey, I’m doing what you said now.

44
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,200
Always arguing with me, huh?

45
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:53,720
Stop! Enough of this!

46
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,960
Hey, hey! What are you doing?!

47
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:57,400
Throw them away!

48
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,720
Why?

49
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:01,040
It’s not up to standard!

50
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:03,880
The recipe is still a work in progress.
Just chill out.

51
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,920
My café is not a lab

52
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:12,120
where you can experiment
whenever you feel like it!

53
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,440
I talked to Auntie Phailin.

54
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:16,079
Go talk to her yourself.

55
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:18,120
Don’t hide behind my mom.

56
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:20,440
When will you stop picking on me?

57
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,840
I’m being honest!

58
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,040
Your banana cake is trash!

59
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:26,800
That’s it!

60
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:30,640
Stop fighting! DinDin! Stop!

61
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:34,480
Why can't you two talk like adults?!

62
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,360
I’m sorry, Auntie Phailin.

63
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:43,760
Can't you two just keep this civil?

64
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,480
About the cakes,

65
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:47,840
I allowed DinDin to do it!

66
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,160
I don't know

67
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:52,000
what's going on between you two,

68
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:53,800
but while you're at work,

69
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:56,480
can you please talk nicely?

70
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:04,600
Tawan! Tawan!

71
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,320
Keep making them.

72
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:13,360
Yes.

73
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:25,200
-I've taken the lead.
-Oh!

74
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,760
-Who threw that?
<i>-Pi Doc!</i>

75
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:28,920
<i>Come play in the water with me!</i>

76
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,800
-Whose clip is that?
-Was that your "Pi Doc?"

77
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,400
How the heck do you know?

78
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:38,360
Well, I heard it.

79
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:40,080
How far have you guys gone?

80
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:43,200
We’re… just talking.

81
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:50,920
Hey, do you know how he feels about me?

82
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:53,120
Why?

83
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:57,640
He told me "I’m cute."

84
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:00,880
Does he say that to everyone?

85
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:01,880
You think so?

86
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:06,000
I doubt he tells everyone they're cute.

87
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:09,120
Hey, he’s a psychiatrist.

88
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,160
He knows what people want to hear.

89
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:13,960
Still, the doctor is a busy guy.

90
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:18,200
But he invited you for dinner
and a talk. I think he's into you.

91
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:20,960
Don’t give him false hope, Lemon.

92
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,640
Maybe psychiatrists have a way…

93
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:26,280
to play mind games?
Have you guys even touched yet?

94
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:31,160
What the hell is wrong with you?

95
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,840
Hey, I’m speaking the truth.

96
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:36,320
Alright! Stop rubbing it in!

97
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,720
I won’t text him.

98
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:48,880
Who texted you? Was that the doctor?

99
00:06:56,120 --> 00:07:01,400
"Are you free tomorrow? I’d love
to show you around Pattaya again."

100
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,200
There! He likes you!

101
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:05,160
He's just being polite.

102
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:18,320
WANNA CALL?

103
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:26,240
Get out!

104
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:28,280
Where are your manners?

105
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:30,080
Oh, you…

106
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:31,640
Come on, let’s go.

107
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:34,200
-Move it.
-Move fast!

108
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:45,680
<i>Did you enjoy our bike ride?</i>

109
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:49,400
I did, Pi Doc. I felt like…

110
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,240
I got to see the real Pattaya.

111
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,920
<i>Since you've been back from the US,</i>

112
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,480
<i>have you been anywhere with your friends?</i>

113
00:07:56,280 --> 00:08:01,880
Not really. My friends are gamers,
and I'm not a fan of crowded places.

114
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:04,840
And what are you doing right now?

115
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:07,560
Packing my things.

116
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:12,560
I understand. I've been through
some tough times myself.

117
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:15,840
<i>But we'll get through it,</i>
<i>one way or another.</i>

118
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:21,120
Are all psychiatrists
such positive thinkers?

119
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,680
Pi Doc.

120
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,240
<i>Pi Doc.</i>

121
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:43,960
<i>Pi Doc?</i>

122
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:45,240
<i>Pi Doc.</i>

123
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:47,840
<i>Yes?</i>

124
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:50,880
<i>I’m sorry.</i>

125
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:53,440
<i>Are you okay?</i>

126
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,400
<i>I’m fine.</i>

127
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,880
I was lost in some old memories.

128
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:02,560
<i>And… where will you take me tomorrow?</i>

129
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:05,720
<i>I'm not telling.</i>

130
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:08,080
<i>It's a surprise.</i>

131
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:13,280
Alright, see you then.

132
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:14,960
Bye-bye.

133
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:20,120
Dude, he’s stringing you along.

134
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,200
Just ask him if he’s seeing anyone.

135
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,440
Are you nuts?

136
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:26,400
Yes, make things clear
so he stops being so vague.

137
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:12,440
I haven’t gone cycling with
my family for a long time.

138
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,600
Why?

139
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:16,840
Well…

140
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:19,760
I usually went cycling with my family.

141
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:25,400
But as everyone grew up
and started working,

142
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:28,080
we haven't really done it lately.

143
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:35,040
Since I came back,
I haven’t met my dad either.

144
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:41,120
He’s my family, but everyone
has their own life. Right, Pi Doc?

145
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:49,240
The whole city view is beautiful.

146
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:05,480
It would be even better with a lover.

147
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:09,840
Bring your girlfriend next time.

148
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,280
Are you crazy?! I don’t have one!

149
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:15,840
I can’t even let people touch me.

150
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:20,080
And…

151
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:21,240
what about you?

152
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:23,760
Do you have one?

153
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:28,160
Just broke up with her.

154
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:33,960
I’m sorry about that.

155
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:36,600
That’s okay.

156
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:38,880
I have already moved on.

157
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,240
That’s kind of quick.

158
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:46,200
Why did you two break up?

159
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:53,880
I proposed to her.

160
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:59,640
And she said she would work in Vietnam.

161
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:02,880
So, she denied me.

162
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:07,720
I’m not sure if she…

163
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:12,760
denied me because of her work
or if we just weren't meant to be.

164
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,240
I think…

165
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:19,240
she didn’t want you to wait for her.

166
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:21,360
That’s why.

167
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:25,840
I guess so.

168
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:32,920
What about you? Never had a girlfriend?

169
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:37,840
Yes, I haven’t!

170
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:40,600
I’ve never had one.

171
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:45,000
With my conditions,

172
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:47,840
I’m scared that people won’t…

173
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:52,440
accept what I have.

174
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:58,560
Sailom, It’s okay to be scared.

175
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:00,920
There’s nothing wrong with that.

176
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:04,200
Sometimes, it’s better to be scared.

177
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:08,760
Fear just makes you more careful

178
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,680
about starting a relationship.

179
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,280
Do you really think that way?

180
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:18,040
Yes.

181
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:45,000
It would be awesome… if more people
go cycling with us. We won’t be lonely.

182
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:49,960
How about we start a trip?

183
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:06,680
Okay, now we’ll start the drink bidding!

184
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,880
Number 69, 60 drinks!

185
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:11,560
Oh, wow! Our Sky gets 60 drinks--

186
00:14:11,640 --> 00:14:14,960
-Eighty.
-Eighty drinks! Going once--

187
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:16,480
200 drinks!

188
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:18,920
And here’s 200 drinks! Going once--

189
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:22,440
-210!
-210 drinks! Going once--

190
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:25,680
-Make it 299!
-299! Going once!

191
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,240
Twice--

192
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,320
350!

193
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:32,200
350 drinks! Going once… twice--

194
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,480
355!

195
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:34,840
355 drinks--

196
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:38,840
-Make it 400!
-400! Now, it’s 400! Any higher bids?

197
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:41,040
Going once… twice…

198
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:45,080
And sold! Off you go to the table, Sky!

199
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:47,240
Now, he’s off the floor!

200
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,640
Is all this really necessary?

201
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:52,320
For taking me back to my room.

202
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:55,280
Did you really have to
compete with Pi Man that much?

203
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:58,120
I don't like people touching what's mine.

204
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:08,480
Does this mean… I’m yours?

205
00:15:09,160 --> 00:15:12,400
It means… I just want you
to stay by my side.

206
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:31,440
Your reward.

207
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:41,480
Surprise!

208
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:42,720
Wow!

209
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:44,760
What is this?

210
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:46,920
Oh!

211
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,720
What is this?

212
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:55,400
The money garland for
the four-kids best mom.

213
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:58,800
Oh, does it have to be this grand?

214
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:00,840
Is this a Songkran day?

215
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:03,400
Actually, I just got my commission.

216
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:08,480
I’ve been saving up for 15 days
to help you with the shops rent.

217
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:11,520
So nice of you. Thank you.

218
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:12,440
Let me hug you.

219
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:16,800
So refreshing.

220
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,640
Now, you’re the favorite son.

221
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,640
Can I be her favorite one sometime?

222
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:24,080
I’m always back home late
and have to work at night.

223
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:26,760
Unlike you, you’re always with her.

224
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:28,440
That was a sarcastic kiss.

225
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:32,680
If Sky is your favorite son,
what about me?

226
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:35,440
Aww.

227
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:37,840
I love you all equally.

228
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,520
-Oh, Sky.
-Yes?

229
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:46,240
Don’t forget to rest.

230
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:50,360
And don’t drink too much booze,
or you’ll get a hard liver.

231
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:51,480
Alright.

232
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:52,800
Yep, the favorite son.

233
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:55,520
Now, Mom lectures you.

234
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:59,880
And you. You're not a host,
but you drink day and night.

235
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:00,800
Keep lecturing him, Mom.

236
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:02,480
Didn’t you lecture him?

237
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,800
Why does it come back to me?

238
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:08,040
How to unwrap these?

239
00:17:08,119 --> 00:17:12,839
You want to unwrap them? It took me
all day to make the garland this big!

240
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:15,160
I must use the money.

241
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:17,960
And look, I’ve turned into a lizard!

242
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:19,280
I’ll help you unwrap them.

243
00:17:19,359 --> 00:17:21,440
If I help, can I have a share?

244
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:23,599
Hey, stop right there. No.

245
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:25,480
-Can I have some?
-No way! You can’t!

246
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:30,400
What?

247
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:31,760
"A Heart-Healing Trip."

248
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:36,280
Just checking in to see who’s up
for a cycling trip to heal the soul.

249
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,440
What’s this, bro?

250
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:40,040
A cycling trip.

251
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,360
A cycling trip?

252
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:42,400
Yep.

253
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:43,880
What gets into you?

254
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,880
I’m thinking of organizing a cycling trip.

255
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:52,800
We have a bicycle café. We should invite
people who are interested to join.

256
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,480
What do you think?

257
00:17:55,080 --> 00:17:56,160
Good idea.

258
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:58,440
I’ll invite customers from my club.

259
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:01,680
Good. I’ll invite my patients to join.

260
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:05,800
I’m in.
I’ll invite customers from the shop.

261
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:09,000
I’ll invite customers from the café.

262
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:11,680
-Right, Mom?
-Yes, Sweetie.

263
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:12,760
Let’s unwrap this.

264
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:14,920
Shall we?

265
00:18:15,520 --> 00:18:17,480
-Gentle… be careful.
-Mom…

266
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:18,880
Can I borrow some?

267
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:23,240
It's for Mom!

268
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:40,680
Nava.

269
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:44,760
How can you come here?

270
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:46,120
I’m on a break.

271
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:48,800
I saw your story and decided to drop by.

272
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:50,640
Are you drunk?

273
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,280
No.

274
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:53,880
Are you sure?

275
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,280
Not yet.

276
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:56,640
You sure?

277
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:01,400
Wanna go cycling this Saturday?

278
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:06,560
-Cycling?
-My family’s café is organizing a trip.

279
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:16,320
I’ve wanted to go on a trip
but… I never got a chance.

280
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:17,960
Then come with me.

281
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:20,600
-Okay.
-Cheers.

282
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:28,640
If you’re free,
please join us on the trip.

283
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:31,200
-Sure thing. Thanks for the invite.
-No problem.

284
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:32,920
Sounds interesting. Which day?

285
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,000
This Saturday.

286
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:34,920
A HEART HEALING TRIP
COME AND JOIN A BIKE TRIP TOGETHER

287
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,520
It’s a chill ride to enjoy the view.

288
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:39,400
I'll join if I'm free.

289
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:41,600
-Sounds interesting!
-Yes, it's intersting!

290
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:46,800
Are you guys free?

291
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:48,240
Make yourselves free for this.

292
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:50,800
It's the "Heart-Healing Trip."

293
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:54,560
Over 50 people have signed up.
I'm organizing it.

294
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:57,120
So, come join us if you can.

295
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:59,120
That's good. It sounds interesting.

296
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:03,240
I haven't cycled in ages.
I'll need to warm up.

297
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:06,360
Alright, are we ready?

298
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:10,880
If you don’t have any plans,
come cycling with us this Saturday.

299
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:15,760
Do you think you can handle the ride?

300
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:17,240
Of course!

301
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:19,840
‎Alright!

302
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,840
Wooh!

303
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:33,560
Damn, Pi Nabnueng!
Tons of people are interested.

304
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:35,400
Look at all these sign-ups.

305
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:38,120
-Of course.
-You’re the man, Bro.

306
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:43,000
Hey, we haven’t
hung out like this in ages.

307
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:46,360
-Let’s have a toast!
-What are we waiting for?

308
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,520
-Hey, Bro. About this trip…
-Yes?

309
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:55,280
you do this to…

310
00:20:55,360 --> 00:21:00,720
heal your own heart?

311
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:05,920
Yeah, you’ve been looking stressed.
Can you really move on from Yanin?

312
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:12,600
-I can.
-What?! With who? Tell me!

313
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:14,600
-That’s quick.
-Hey,

314
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,560
does it have to be someone?

315
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:18,120
I’m working!

316
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,600
Haven’t you heard?

317
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:21,360
"Just focus on work."

318
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:23,440
-Aww…
-Yeah, work…

319
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:25,200
-But Looksoh said…
-What?

320
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:26,760
you went cycling with an American guy.

321
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,240
What guy? No, you’re wrong!

322
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:31,320
Are you sure?

323
00:21:32,920 --> 00:21:34,400
He's just a kid!

324
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:36,280
I see…

325
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:39,160
Who is that kid?

326
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:41,280
His name is Sailom.

327
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:42,640
He’s just a kid.

328
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:44,320
But he has…

329
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:46,240
a condition.

330
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:49,320
Haphephobia.

331
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:50,880
You can’t touch him like this.

332
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,320
-No touching?
-Yep.

333
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:53,680
How can you date him?

334
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:57,240
I…

335
00:21:57,760 --> 00:21:59,480
I must… treat him first.

336
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:02,600
Ah, so if you…

337
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:05,600
If you date him,

338
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:09,160
do you have to keep your distance
like this when you have sex with him?

339
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:10,520
‎-Wait!
‎-Come on!

340
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:15,440
That would hurt like hell
if you hit there. Sorry. Just teasing.

341
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,800
You were so bold.

342
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:21,080
I know. I was teasing him.

343
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:22,400
What about you?!

344
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:25,560
-Look at him deflecting.
-Yeah.

345
00:22:26,840 --> 00:22:29,160
Got someone yet?
You’ve been awfully quiet lately.

346
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:32,080
Yeah, What's the deal? Spill it.

347
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:37,040
I fix bicycles.
I don’t have time for that.

348
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:44,040
What about… your favorite little brother?

349
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:48,160
Hardly stays home.
Probably gets clingy with a customer.

350
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:51,320
What? No, I don’t have anyone!

351
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:54,560
I never get attached to customers, Bro.

352
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:55,960
They get attached to me.

353
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:57,280
Woah!

354
00:22:58,600 --> 00:22:59,840
So cool!

355
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:02,160
Total Sigma Male energy!

356
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:06,440
-Damn, I’m proud of you.
-No doubt!

357
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:07,960
Awesome.

358
00:23:08,040 --> 00:23:09,320
Damn!

359
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:11,080
But seriously…

360
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:16,240
I want to quit being a host.

361
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:17,800
Quit?

362
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:19,520
-Uh-huh
-Why?

363
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:24,440
I feel like…

364
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:29,520
I'm getting too
emotionally involved lately.

365
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:32,120
But deep down, in reality…

366
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,920
There's no way we could
ever have a real relationship.

367
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:40,640
You get what I mean?

368
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:42,280
Are you even listening?

369
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:49,280
Oh, come on.

370
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:04,560
Still better than feeling
something but pretending you don't.

371
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:15,040
He's acting weird.

372
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:16,720
Big time.

373
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:23,920
The hell is weird? Cheers!

374
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,280
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

375
00:24:25,360 --> 00:24:27,880
Nice dodge. I'll let it slide for now.

376
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:34,960
Are you serious about quitting?

377
00:24:35,560 --> 00:24:37,040
Of course!

378
00:24:37,120 --> 00:24:39,200
-He’s just drunk.
-Hey, Bro!

379
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:41,680
The money is great, but…

380
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:43,760
I don’t want to do this forever.

381
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:48,120
-Obsess with a customer, for sure.
-Customer…

382
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:52,640
My ass! I’m not attached to them.
They’re attached to me.

383
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:53,560
Roger that!

384
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:03,760
BRING YOUR FRIENDS ALONG TOO.

385
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:06,760
SURE THING, PI DOC.

386
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:10,600
Wow, look at that grin.

387
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:12,960
Is it your Pi Doc again?

388
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:17,440
Yeah, you're so nosy.
Anyway, come cycling with me.

389
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:19,120
Cycling?

390
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:20,760
Yep.

391
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,600
It's Pi Doc’s cycling trip.

392
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:25,520
I already signed you up.

393
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:30,000
Are you kidding? Do I look like a cyclist?

394
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:32,080
Guys, give me a hand.

395
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:38,120
Why did you buy so much stuff?

396
00:25:38,720 --> 00:25:40,680
Oh, like you eat any less.

397
00:25:40,760 --> 00:25:43,960
We're eating at home for your safety.
So you don't have to bump into anyone.

398
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:47,240
-What about the ice?
-Go get it yourself.

399
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:48,760
Hey, I'm playing a game now.

400
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:50,720
Look at this guy!

401
00:25:51,320 --> 00:25:53,600
-I’m chatting with Pi Doc.
-I'm playing my game.

402
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:01,360
-Cheers! Yay!
-Yay!

403
00:26:09,160 --> 00:26:11,400
So, Sailom…

404
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:13,360
have you slept with him yet?

405
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:14,840
Are you crazy?!

406
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:19,120
When would I even have the chance?
Look at my condition.

407
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:24,280
Ever thought? If you weren't like this,
you might've already been his boyfriend.

408
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:28,920
I have.

409
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:32,680
But I don't know how he feels about me.

410
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:36,320
Why don't you just ask him straight out?

411
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:40,640
If he doesn't feel the same,

412
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:42,400
I'll just look like a fool.

413
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,240
True.

414
00:26:45,080 --> 00:26:48,200
But I think you need to get cured first.

415
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:53,760
Otherwise, you won't be happy
even if you date him. Right?

416
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:58,600
Yeah. If you can't touch
each other, how's it gonna work?

417
00:26:59,280 --> 00:27:02,640
-How are you guys gonna have sex?
-What the hell are you talking about?

418
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:04,440
Am I lying, though?

419
00:27:08,680 --> 00:27:09,640
Fine.

420
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:13,440
How am I supposed to get cured?

421
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:18,040
Didn’t you tell me he's a psychiatrist?

422
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:22,240
Get the treatment and get the guy.

423
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:24,840
Good point.

424
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:28,960
Hey, you guys…

425
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:31,840
Cheers!

426
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:34,320
-Cheers!
-Yay!

427
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:15,080
Sailom!

428
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:24,960
What are you doing here?

429
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:21,800
Sailom.

430
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:23,520
Sailom…

431
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:30,760
Sailom!

432
00:29:33,600 --> 00:29:34,600
Yes?

433
00:29:35,920 --> 00:29:37,280
Are you daydreaming?

434
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:39,080
You even did a "kiss-kiss" face.

435
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:43,280
I was thinking about eating strawberries.

436
00:29:43,360 --> 00:29:44,880
Strawberries.

437
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:46,160
Kiss-kiss.

438
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:50,760
Shall we get started?

439
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:55,800
What made you decide
to seek treatment with me?

440
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:59,280
My friends motivated me.

441
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:03,520
And I really want to get
cured from this condition.

442
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:08,640
I know it won't be easy,

443
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:10,640
and I'm scared.

444
00:30:11,960 --> 00:30:12,800
But…

445
00:30:13,320 --> 00:30:15,400
I don't want to feel this way anymore.

446
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:19,040
And what about the cycling trip?

447
00:30:19,800 --> 00:30:21,040
Have you invited your friends yet?

448
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:23,400
I have.

449
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:26,240
Lemon and James are dying to join.

450
00:30:26,320 --> 00:30:31,360
We're already looking for
a place to practice our riding.

451
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:34,840
Great. You won't get
too tired on the big day.

452
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:38,200
It's going to be very sunny that day.

453
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:45,400
Don't forget to wear sunscreen,
so you don't get burned.

454
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:47,080
This is for you.

455
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:50,480
Thanks.

456
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,600
So, what did you do today?
Tell me about it.

457
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,800
Nothing much, really.

458
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:02,320
Oh, seeing you is the highlight of my day.

459
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:08,200
Uh… I mean, because
I don't get to visit the clinic often.

460
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:14,880
Sailom.

461
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:17,320
Yes?

462
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:26,800
Hello, Mr. Sailom.

463
00:31:27,760 --> 00:31:33,920
I’m Doctor Ying. I’ll be taking over
your case from today on.

464
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:36,720
Right…

465
00:31:37,320 --> 00:31:39,080
How are you doing today?

466
00:31:41,320 --> 00:31:42,520
I’m fine…

467
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:46,600
And… did you sleep well last night?

468
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:49,160
Pretty good…

469
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:52,920
What did you have
for breakfast this morning?

470
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:57,400
Just some coffee and a sandwich.

471
00:31:57,480 --> 00:31:58,720
I see.

472
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:04,680
According to your records,
you’re studying abroad, right?

473
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:08,560
Yes…

474
00:32:09,240 --> 00:32:10,720
I'm studying in the States.

475
00:32:12,280 --> 00:32:14,840
It's summer break now,
so I'm back to stay with my dad.

476
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:17,960
Staying with your father?

477
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:23,080
So, are you originally from Pattaya?

478
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:25,960
<i>Sailom…</i>

479
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:31,200
-This is our new home, Sweetie.
-Yes, Mom.

480
00:32:31,280 --> 00:32:33,520
Oh, you're finally here.

481
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:38,560
Say hello to him, Dear.

482
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:40,360
Hello, Sir.

483
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:41,680
Welcome home, Son.

484
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:45,160
From now on, we're one big family.

485
00:32:45,760 --> 00:32:46,800
Yes, Sir.

486
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:57,400
Eat up, Son.

487
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:01,080
So you can grow up strong.

488
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:17,640
<i>You can always tell me</i>
<i>if you have problems.</i>

489
00:33:54,440 --> 00:33:56,720
Don't you dare tell anyone about this.

490
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:00,160
Or I'll kill your mother.

491
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:55,480
<i>I will teach you.</i>

492
00:36:04,680 --> 00:36:05,840
Sailom…

493
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:09,240
where are you, Son?

494
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:12,600
You’re quite good at hiding.

495
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:18,240
If I catch you…

496
00:36:19,120 --> 00:36:21,000
you’re going to be punished, Son.

497
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:29,840
Could you be right…

498
00:36:53,520 --> 00:36:54,720
What's wrong with you?

499
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:04,680
…Here?!

500
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:06,040
There you are!

501
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:11,400
-Don’t squirm! Come on! Get out!
-Let me go! Let go of me!

502
00:37:17,240 --> 00:37:18,520
Ying…

503
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:20,120
where's Sailom?

504
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:22,560
He left a little while ago.

505
00:37:25,160 --> 00:37:26,440
Look…

506
00:37:26,520 --> 00:37:28,680
he doesn't seem ready at all.

507
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:35,400
Is something bothering you? Or…

508
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:37,360
do you want to take over this case?

509
00:37:38,280 --> 00:37:42,400
No, don't worry about it.
I asked for your help with this one.

510
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:44,720
It’s best if you handle it.

511
00:37:48,160 --> 00:37:49,000
‎Uh-huh.

512
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:56,080
Oh, I have an errand to run. Gotta go.

513
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:58,200
See you later.

514
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:22,600
Hello?

515
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:23,800
<i>Phailin?</i>

516
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:25,720
<i>This is Lada.</i>

517
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:30,120
How is Nabnueng doing?

518
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:35,200
You've got the wrong number.

519
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:30,320
Were you sleeping?

520
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:33,040
Uh-huh?

521
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:34,920
Sleeping on the job, are you?

522
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:38,080
Just resting my eyes.

523
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:41,680
The cookies need to
cool down before packing.

524
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:44,480
Do you even know anything about baking?

525
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:46,080
You were asleep.

526
00:39:52,040 --> 00:39:53,680
Yeah, I was.

527
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:55,760
So what?

528
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:58,000
That's it.

529
00:39:59,080 --> 00:40:00,680
I hired you,

530
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:03,160
but you’re sleeping during working hours?

531
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:06,040
I’m docking your pay.

532
00:40:06,120 --> 00:40:08,760
You're a terrible example for the others.

533
00:40:10,640 --> 00:40:12,400
Whoa, whoa. Hey…

534
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:14,480
Calm down, man.

535
00:40:15,080 --> 00:40:17,640
Calm down? You’re sleeping.

536
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:19,520
You can punch me.

537
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:21,680
Just don't touch my salary.

538
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:24,160
I don't even have enough to get by.

539
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:28,960
Hit me. Just hit me. Right here.

540
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:31,360
Then we’ll be even.

541
00:40:31,440 --> 00:40:35,400
-Let go of me!
-I said punch me!

542
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:40,080
Just don't touch my salary!

543
00:41:16,280 --> 00:41:17,600
Pi DinDin,

544
00:41:21,360 --> 00:41:22,600
are you okay?

545
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:26,360
I'm fine.

546
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:29,440
Take it easy. Don't take
Pi Tawan's words too seriously.

547
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:32,760
He won't actually cut
your pay. It's an empty threat.

548
00:41:32,840 --> 00:41:36,160
He's got a sharp tongue,
but a kind heart. Right, Mickey?

549
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:40,880
Yeah, that's just how he is.
Don't stress out, Pi DinDin.

550
00:41:43,680 --> 00:41:45,080
Okay.

551
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:09,240
-Hello, Pi Man.
-Hey.

552
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:16,320
-Let’s have a drink.
-Alright.

553
00:42:19,480 --> 00:42:20,600
I’ll pour it for you.

554
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:23,800
It’s okay. I’ll do it myself.

555
00:42:27,240 --> 00:42:28,440
Here’s yours.

556
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:31,600
You like it strong.

557
00:42:33,120 --> 00:42:35,160
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

558
00:42:38,720 --> 00:42:41,080
I thought you wouldn’t come.
I saw you were taking a break.

559
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:46,200
You booked me for the whole night.
Of course, I had to come.

560
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:51,280
I missed you, Sky.
Come stay at my place tonight.

561
00:42:52,080 --> 00:42:56,280
Whoa, Pi Man.
You’re not gonna let me go home?

562
00:42:56,800 --> 00:43:01,440
What? You’ve stayed over before.
Why do you want to go home?

563
00:43:05,680 --> 00:43:07,480
-It's just…
-Why?

564
00:43:08,360 --> 00:43:10,000
You don't want to be with me anymore?

565
00:43:11,520 --> 00:43:12,720
It’s not like that--

566
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:13,880
Of course,

567
00:43:14,560 --> 00:43:16,040
you don’t want to.

568
00:43:16,120 --> 00:43:19,360
If I didn't care about you,
why would I be here all night?

569
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:20,360
Cheers to that.

570
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:31,600
Sky…

571
00:43:32,600 --> 00:43:33,440
I thought you were taking a break.

572
00:43:35,560 --> 00:43:36,640
Nava…

573
00:43:39,480 --> 00:43:41,160
Pi Man booked me for the whole night.

574
00:43:43,880 --> 00:43:45,960
Can I help you? This is my table.

575
00:43:47,920 --> 00:43:50,240
My bad. I’m here say hi to Sky.

576
00:43:51,480 --> 00:43:54,280
Where are your manners?
I paid for his time tonight!

577
00:43:55,840 --> 00:43:57,000
So?

578
00:43:57,080 --> 00:43:59,880
I can't say hi to my friend?

579
00:44:01,360 --> 00:44:02,280
Are you looking for trouble?

580
00:44:03,560 --> 00:44:04,520
No, I’m not.

581
00:44:06,480 --> 00:44:09,640
When you booked him,
did I ever get in your way?

582
00:44:13,800 --> 00:44:17,040
-Sky, is that your glass?
-Yeah.

583
00:44:29,280 --> 00:44:30,160
That's enough!

584
00:44:33,960 --> 00:44:35,720
Hey! Nava, stop!

585
00:44:36,240 --> 00:44:38,720
I said stop!

586
00:44:39,480 --> 00:44:40,400
Stop!

587
00:44:43,360 --> 00:44:45,120
Pi Man, please calm down.

588
00:44:46,280 --> 00:44:48,280
-Let's go, Nava.
-Where are you going?!

589
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:50,800
Stay with me! Let him go!

590
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:53,320
Hey, stop!

591
00:44:53,400 --> 00:44:55,520
-Ah!
-Let go of me!

592
00:44:55,600 --> 00:44:56,600
Mr. Man!

593
00:44:56,680 --> 00:44:58,960
Security! Get him out of here! Now!

594
00:44:59,040 --> 00:45:00,560
Please calm down, Mr. Man.

595
00:45:00,640 --> 00:45:02,400
-We’re so sorry.
-I’m so sorry, Mama.

596
00:45:02,480 --> 00:45:04,840
-Take care of him.
-Pi Man, take it easy.

597
00:45:04,920 --> 00:45:08,120
Did you see him?!
He was trying to screw with me!

598
00:45:08,640 --> 00:45:10,240
Why didn't you stand up for me?

599
00:45:10,840 --> 00:45:13,200
Look at me. I'm right here with you.

600
00:45:13,760 --> 00:45:16,320
Please calm down.
Let's go back and have fun.

601
00:45:16,400 --> 00:45:18,200
Hey! Nothing to see here!
Keep the party going!

602
00:45:18,280 --> 00:45:21,240
Let's just go back and have fun, okay?

603
00:45:22,320 --> 00:45:24,400
Let me fill your glass.

604
00:45:25,040 --> 00:45:27,840
I'll even go back to your room tonight.

605
00:45:27,920 --> 00:45:31,120
You're out of drinks.
Let me get you another one.

606
00:45:32,120 --> 00:45:33,320
Hey!

607
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:47,160
<i>What the hell do you want from me now?</i>

608
00:46:47,240 --> 00:46:48,960
-Someone to drink with.
-I'm not drinking.

609
00:46:49,560 --> 00:46:51,960
<i>Tawan might act tough on the outside,</i>

610
00:46:52,040 --> 00:46:54,800
<i>but he’s actually a very kind person.</i>

611
00:46:55,920 --> 00:46:57,400
<i>I'm thinking about quitting the host job.</i>

612
00:46:57,480 --> 00:46:58,400
Why?

613
00:47:00,560 --> 00:47:02,640
<i>What's wrong?</i>
<i>You've been spacing out all morning.</i>

614
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:05,440
<i>Can you tell me what's going on?</i>

615
00:47:05,520 --> 00:47:07,360
<i>Why did you decide to stop the treatment?</i>

616
00:47:07,440 --> 00:47:10,360
<i>If this treatment is like</i>
<i>riding a bike, just like you said.</i>

617
00:47:10,440 --> 00:47:13,360
Now, you’ve cycled
far away and left me behind.
